test_1005,3,11,"Ha, that's so cute. I bet he's sweet. Have you been to any good restaurants lately? We eat out often so I'm always looking for something new to try."
test_1006,3,0,My mother and I rode into Columbus today. I saw a cool Five Finger Death Punch shirt.
test_1006,3,1,Awesome! I could do with another of their tshirts... I might see if I can get one next time I see them live. Do you have any plans to go to any music gigs soon?
test_1006,3,2,Not at the moment.  I need to look at the summer concert calendar and figure something out.  How about you?  Do you have anything on your radar?
test_1006,3,3,"No, I haven't got anything booked yet. I should really start looking as I haven't been to a gig in ages. There's nothing quite like live music!"
test_1006,3,4,I agree.  It's such an incredible experience to be in a big crowd with everyone enjoying the same music.  What was the first concert you ever went to?  I think mine was a Raffi concert at a fair.
test_1006,3,5,"Yea, the crowd atmosphere is just amazing! Was Raffi good? The first concert I ever went to was when I was very young and it was something my parents liked, so I can't even remember what it was. One artist I always wish I had seen is David Bowie. Is there any music artist you wish you could have seen before they passed away?"
test_1006,3,6,"Oh, wow, that's a good question.  I suppose I would have liked to see Kurt Cobain play with Nirvana.  That would have been cool.  And yes, as a five-year-old I loved Raffy!"
test_1006,3,7,"Yea that's a great answer, I think a Nirvana concert would have been amazing. Kurt Cobain died really young didn't he... there are so many famous people who lose their lives early, it's such a shame. I'm glad you loved the concert as a little one!"
test_1006,3,8,For sure.  So how have car sales been for you recently?
test_1006,3,9,"It's been alright actually, not loads but there's a steady stream. More people are wanting SUVs at the moment, as it seems they want something they can go on adventurous road trips with. Do you own a car?"
test_1006,3,10,"Yes, I have a little Honda hatchback.  It's pretty old and beat up at this point.  When I'm looking for a replacement maybe you can help me find something."
test_1006,3,11,"Yea for sure, I can give you advice even if we don't have the right kind of car in stock for you. Honda hatchbacks are great reliable cars; good choice!"
test_1010,3,0,My boss decided to give me another chance since this was my first accident at work. I am so relieved.
test_1010,3,1,So happy to hear that too! I hope your boss doesn't end up like the pointy-haired one from Dilbert!
test_1010,3,2,"Haha no he's not, thank god. I feel so lucky to still be in my job, but it really was an accident and to be honest the fact I'm not injured is a miracle! But anyway, how is art life going? Have you sold any paintings recently?"
test_1010,3,3,"It's not going the best; I've only sold three quick-and-cheap paintings in a week. But I don't overspend, so I'm taking it quite easy. "
test_1010,3,4,"Well done for selling three though, that's certainly better than nothing! I don't think I've ever asked you what kind of things you like to paint?"
test_1010,3,5,"I'm a plein air kind of person. Love watercolors and oil painting equally, but apart from that quite conservative in style. About your boss, how's his personality?"
test_1010,3,6,"I always find watercolor paintings so calming to look at, there's something really delicate about them. Well I hope sales pick up soon. So my boss is one of those people who comes across as a tough guy until you get to know him a bit better. Then you get to see his sense of humor and realise he's quite down to earth. Do you like not having a boss? "
test_1010,3,7,"Ehh...now that you mention it, I like the freedom, but in a sense dislike having no one to talk to. (But I do live within my means, so self employment isn't too nerve racking)"
test_1011,3,0,When's the last time you went on a cruise?
test_1011,3,1,"I think it was about two years ago; I have to save up quite a bit for each one so it takes me a while. Hopefully, by next year, I'll have enough to book my another cruise."
test_1011,3,2,I was thinking that I might start saving up to go on a cruise.  Do you have any recommendations for destinations?
test_1011,3,3,"My last cruise was to the Caribbean and I had a blast, but this time I'm saving to go to Alaska. I think it mainly depends on what type of activities you're hoping to do. Is there anything specific you're hoping to experience? "
test_1011,3,4,"I'm not sure.  Do you think more of the value of the cruise comes from the things to do on the ship itself, or from the place you're going?"
test_1011,3,5,"I like both aspects of cruising - that I can see several different places on one trip and that I don't have to worry about transportation, food, or nighttime entertainment."
test_1011,3,6,Is there any worry of getting seasick?  I got seasick one time as a kid and don't want to experience that again.  Are the cruise ships too big to have to worry about that?
test_1011,3,7,"I don't usually get motion sickness, but we did hit a storm one night on my last cruise and I definitely felt it then. Maybe invest in some dramamine or a motion sickness bracelet? Also, I would think that a bigger ship might be a better option for you so there is less chance of you feeling it. Is motion sickness usually a problem for you? Or just on the water? "
test_1011,3,8,"I've never had a problem in a car or airplane, just in a boat one time.  But that was enough to never want to feel it again.  I could definitely get some dramamine.  I didn't realize there were motion sickness bracelets.  Have you ever used either?"
test_1011,3,9,"I've never used either of them, but the dramamine worked out well for the friend who went with me. Was the boat you were on smaller? Like a fishing boat or sail boat? I would hate for you to run the risk of being sick the whole time, but I really think that you would enjoy the cruise."
test_1011,3,10,"Yes, it was a fishing boat.  We went out deep sea fishing and I spent the entire trip hanging over the railing of the boat.  Not sure if my breakfast attracted fish or not."
test_1011,3,11,"Wow! That would probably put me off boats for a while too. But you said it happend when you were younger, right? Maybe give a bigger sailboat a try to see if you've outgrown it?"
test_1014,3,0,How are the paintings coming along?
test_1014,3,1,Great thank you! And how about your brewing skills... did you learn some new techniques?
test_1014,3,2,"I am reading a book about steeping coffee right now. It is really interesting.  Once I learn more about brewing coffee, I would like to organize a coffee tasting events."
test_1014,3,3,"Oh I would love that! Must be my italian roots. I love love love coffee. I recently bought a new coffee machine, but I don't know if I would have the patience to brew."
test_1014,3,4,It takes time but those new machines make good coffee too! How is your family doing?
