test_261,4,2,"Is it ok to use the Teleportation Device for such trivial purposes? I would be reliving yesterday incessantly to get things perfect, just like Bill Murray in Groundhog Day"
test_261,4,3,"Yeah, it's probably not the best idea to keep doing that. Might go crazy! What kind of dog is Einstein?"
test_261,4,4,"Einstein is a mutt, a Frankenstein concotion of many breeds. Einstein is smart, but even he can't figure out his pedigree. "
test_261,4,5,LOL you could always try one of those dog DNA tests. Or just leave Einstein a mystery.
test_261,4,6,"My dog enjoys his air of mystery. He uses it to pick up other dogs at hipster dog cafes. He claims that he only drinks artisinal toilet water, but I know he drinks tap water."
test_261,4,7,"Ahh, I definitely see the appeal of the mysteriousness. He'll probably grow out of that hipster stage - they always do."
test_261,4,8,"They slow down and start looking too gray in the muzzle. ""Act your age!"" I tell Einstein. He thinks he can be young forever, but even the best teleportation devices can only take us back one day. "
test_261,4,9,Well HOPEFULLY I can get mine to take me back further. I can't quite figure out how yet but I've been working incessantly at it.
test_261,4,10,The problem is the power source. You need orders of magnitude more power. It's just not available on this conventional grid. Power tech needs to catch up to YOU>
test_261,4,11,You're completely right. I've been waiting for a lightening storm to try and harvest that power (I've watched Back to the Future far too many times). But there are no storms in the near future according to the weather channel.
test_264,4,0,Are you planning to go to any country music concerts in the near future? 
test_264,4,1,"I haven't thought about it too much, but now that it's warming up, there will be a lot more shows, so I'll do a bit of research to see who will be here this summer. What about you?"
test_264,4,2,"Oh yes, I will be out at shows all summer long! Cannot wait! Who are some of your favorites?"
test_264,4,3,"Haha well a lot of my favorites are from a bygone era, but I'm rather impressed with the singer songwriter Ingrid Andress. I'm thinking I might go to a few of her shows if she puts on any this summer. What shows are you planning to attend?"
test_264,4,4,"Ingrid Andress is a star in the making. Lady like is a straight up jam! First and foremost King George Strait is my favorite always a good time to listen to him, lately I've been jamming hard to luke combs and Jordan Davis"
