test_273,4,7,"Yes, cats can definitely be temperamental.  They consider themselves the boss...lol.  Zoey is very easy-going, however, and the kids love her.  So tell me about your raccoon.  "
test_273,4,8,"My raccoon's name is Bandito, for obvious reasons. They actually get along with the bearded dragon pretty well; they'll kind of just stare at each other. And Bandito knows not to mess with the horses"
test_273,4,9,"Lol!  I just got a visual image of the bearded dragon and Bandito staring at each other, sizing each other up.  I love that name for a raccoon.  Perfect."
test_273,4,10,"Yeah, I had to get a stronger enclosure for the bearded dragon, though. One time Bandito charged at the old one and shattered it; it was a mess. He only tried once with the new one and learned his lessons. So how did you end up writing children's books? Had you always wanted to or did you just find it to be a good outlet?"
test_273,4,11,"I've always loved to write, and found it came naturally.  Also, I had lots of stories based on my own children and their antics...lol"
test_279,4,0,Have you see or killed any big gators lately?
test_279,4,1,Yes! I've had to remove a couple from some golf courses in the area and one that had crawled up right into someone's yard! That's the danger of living on the water in Florida!
