test_870,4,1,That sounds good! I really need to get out more and meet more people. Is there any veggies or dishes you'd like me to bring in particular?
test_870,4,2,"Fantastic, I am so excited that you will be able to make it. I think we are set to provide all of the main dishes and barbeque, but if you would like to bring a dessert that would be so appreciated! "
test_870,4,3,"Oooh, a desert? I can't lie, I don't really have a lot of experience with making veggie desserts. I guess I can try to whip something up, but I'm nervous no one will like it!"
test_870,4,4,"How interesting! I do not believe I have ever had a dessert that wasn't vegetarian - and I am struggling to even think of a dessert dish which contains meat. No matter, I do not want the party to be a burden on you. You can bring disposable cutlery and plates, if that will be easier."
test_870,4,5,"Well, a lot of desserts have gelatin and things like that in them that are animal based. I'm not vegan, but I try to avoid a lot of animal based products, just because I don't like how they are manufactured."
test_870,4,6,"Okay, sounds great! Will you be bringing your kids to the weekend barbeque? If they aren't with your ex-wife then I would love to see them."
test_870,4,7,"I will have to check in with her and see if she would be alright with that. I don't see why she would have a problem with it, though. I'd like them to have a chance to meet more kids from my neighborhood. "
test_870,4,8,"Great, I hope that they can make it. There will be quite a few other kids at the barbeque. Could you please remind me of their ages? I am trying to think if there will be kids there of similar age."
test_870,4,9,"I have a son, and he's 8. He's growing up so fast I can barely keep up lately, and it makes having all this space between us very difficult. "
test_870,4,10,What a fun age! There will definitely be other 8-10 year olds at the barbeque for him to play with. This will be a great time for you two to bond. Has he gotten any better at eating his vegetables?
test_870,4,11,"Honestly, no. His mother feeds him all kinds of junk, so I feel like as soon as I make any progress with him, she just undoes all the hard work. "
test_873,4,0,I'm just glad to be home and relax a bit.
test_873,4,1,Did you have a busy day?
test_873,4,2,"Every day is a busy day.  I envy you and your jobs, working with children has to be more emotionally rewarding than what I do!"
test_873,4,3,"It can be very emotionally rewarding, but still often stressful. Children have so much energy, they can be a handful!"
test_873,4,4,"No doubt, but having human contact is more fulfilling than working mostly with numbers.  I think that maybe working with my hands would improve my quality of life."
test_873,4,5,Maybe! Have you considered changing careers?
test_873,4,6,"It's more of a daydream than a plan.  On a more pragmatic level, I've got a great boss and don't want to let him down by leaving."
test_873,4,7,Maybe you can buffer the stress of working in a less hands-on field by taking on a tactile hobby!
test_873,4,8,"I already do to some extent, I work on improving my house when I have some free time."
test_873,4,9,That's awesome! Do you have any other hobbies?
test_873,4,10,"I enjoy making simple, sturdy furniture, mostly just for myself and friends and family."
test_873,4,11,"Oh! So do you like woodworking, then?"
test_876,4,0,Have you seen anything interesting in the sky recently?
test_876,4,1,"Yes. I always see strange appearances, almost every night. Probably the government. Probably aliens. Probably both. I can never say for sure, but there is a lot they aren't telling us, that is for sure."
test_876,4,2,I agree!  I have seen several things in the sky that looked suspicious.  I definitely believe in aliens...
test_876,4,3,I believe too... THEY'RE OUT THERE. I wonder when and where aliens will make first contact - if they haven't yet already? Mind boggling. Have you seen any interesting as of late? 
test_876,4,4,"I actually saw something in the sky the other night as I was driving.  It didn't look like a plane, and it had a lot of lights.  I stopped my car, and it stopped too!  That freaked me out, so I got back in my car.  It started going when I did.  Weird.  How about you?  Have you seen anything weird?"
test_876,4,5,"Did you manage to get any pictures? Please tell me you did! I see strange events almost every night, but last week I saw a small ball of light that appeared like it came up over the lake, and stayed suspended there for minutes. Then out of nowhere, it zipped straight up into the sky and disappeared!"
test_876,4,6,"Wow.  That is really wild.  Unfortunately, I did not get any pictures. I wish I had!"
test_876,4,7,"I always try to take pictures and videos of every event I observe. I can send some over if you'd like, maybe you can help me analyze some of them? I'm trying to make written reports for each of them so I can publish them online."
test_876,4,8,"Oh wow.  That would be awesome!  I have not gone so far as to do any of that, but now I think I will.  I would love to see what you have!"
test_876,4,9,"I've got years of footage that I need to sort through. I could really use the help, honestly. Are you in any Facebook groups related to star watching or ufo sightings? I'm in a lot of them, I could invite you to them if you'd like."
test_876,4,10,"Oh, please do!  I am not a member of any, and didn't even know there were any...lol.  I'm so behind!"
test_876,4,11,"Don't worry about it - not a lot of people are aware these groups exist. We share a lot of information with each other, and it's a lot of fun. I'll send you a few invites when I get a free minute to check my Facebook."
test_878,4,0,I just made a new vegetarian dish I think you should try.
test_878,4,1,Oh that's interesting? What's the dish?
test_878,4,2,It was based around beets and mushrooms with a nice dressing. I will send you the recipe! Maybe you can share one with me as well?
test_878,4,3,"I've been experimenting with some new ideas, but sadly none of them are vegetarian. Do you like tacos?"
test_878,4,4,"That is ok! I can figure out my own substitutes for your recipes. I love tacos, vegan of course! "
test_878,4,5,I've been working on this idea for deconstructed fish tacos. Can vegetarians have fish?
test_878,4,6,"That sounds interesting! Can't wait to see it come to life! Some vegetarians eat some fish, but vegan do not. "
test_878,4,7,"Oh! I am so sorry, That was inconsiderate of me! I have also been working on a new Japchae recipe that I could probably substitute the meat with tofu if that would be better!"
test_878,4,8,"Not at all, no need to be sorry! I am only newly trying to eat healthy and respect others food choses. Like I mentioned prior, I enjoy taking a recipe idea and making it my own. "
test_878,4,9,"That's so cool! I am glad you're considerate of others food choices, I think I could learn a thing or two from you! Would you like to cook together at some point to see if we could put our minds together to make something interesting and new?"
test_878,4,10,Oh I love the idea. Let me know when you are thinking and I will be there! I am sure we could come up with some great dishes! 
test_878,4,11,That would be so fun! Have you been teaching jiu-jitsu a lot recently?
test_880,4,0,Have you done anything fund with your grandchildren?
test_880,4,1,We went to the beach last weekend! It is a good thing to do with them because everyone can enjoy it at any age.
test_880,4,2,You do have arrange of ages. Do the younger ones still like building sandcastles?
test_880,4,3,"The 7 year old does, but the others say that is for babies. They are at that age where they are desperate be adults!"
test_880,4,4,I get that. Did you bring sandwiches? I love a picnic at the beach. 
test_880,4,5,I do! Those kids always seem to be hungry! Speaking of...what are you having for dinner tonight?
test_880,4,6,I have pulled pork in the slow cooker. I'm planning to have that with nice buns. It's too hot to cook. 
test_880,4,7,"That sounds delicious! I don't have any food, so I might just get a pizza."
test_880,4,8,That sounds yum. What topping do you normal order? I like pepperoni the best
test_880,4,9,"I love ham and pineapple. Most people hate it, but it is my favorite!"
test_880,4,10,Each to their own. As long as I don't have to eat any. haha
test_880,4,11,Fair enough! Give it a try sometime when you are feeling brave!
test_883,4,0,I just got this order for a crochet fish that you HAVE to see!
test_883,4,1,"Oh, how exciting!! Congratulations on getting an order, I am so happy that your Etsy shop is doing well. What kind of crochet fish is the order for?"
test_883,4,2,They just wanted this multi-colored one with the button eyes that I put on them. They're very cute and make really great gifts for kids. I'm really hoping that the Esty business will pick up because I think it would be great for supplementing my income.
test_883,4,3,"How cute! You will have to send a photo of that order to me prior to shipping it out. If you could do Etsy full-time, would you take the opportunity and quit your travel agency job?"
test_883,4,4,"I'll definitely send a photo over - do you think you might be interested in one? And, I'm unsure if I'd quit being a travel agent. The perks are really great, and I have a great connection with my clientele. Not to mention, they have been a great way of funneling traffic to my Etsy business! "
test_883,4,5,"Oh, how interesting. I had not considered using the travel agency to get more clients for your business. How do you advertise your crochet to your travel clients?"
test_883,4,6,"I have a very close, almost friend connection with a lot of my clients. So, when they seem they are eager to learn more about the things I do, I share it with them. You'd be surprised how many people from my client base actually express interest in my personal life. "
test_883,4,7,That is great to hear that you are so close with your clients. What a testimony to your excellent service! What are the majority of your crochet orders for? Do you do different animals and sizes?
test_883,4,8,"I've gotten a lot of orders for crocheted blankets, and those are usually the most expensive. The crochet fish are new, but I'm hoping people will show more interest in them. I was considering doing other animals, do you have any recommendations? "
test_883,4,9,"Wow, you are so talented to be able to create so many different crochet crafts. I do not know much about crochet or how difficult different patterns would be, but I think a bee crochet pattern would be really cute and popular. I have seen photo examples on Pinterest."
test_883,4,10,"Do you have any links you can show me? Maybe I'll make a test design, and if it's any good, you can keep it!"
test_883,4,11,"Yes, I will send the links over to you via email. They are big round bees with little tiny wings, they look very cute. Do you usually use a pattern when you crochet or do you do it free hand?"
test_885,4,0,Have you tried anything new for your mother's restaurant?
test_885,4,1,I have. She has a new spicy soup that's very popular.
test_885,4,2,I love soups. What's in it?
test_885,4,3,It's a clear spicy chicken broth. I'll have to ask my mum for the recipe. 
test_885,4,4,That sounds delicious. Lucky you getting to test the new items!
test_885,4,5,I am lucky. How are your vegetables coming along now?
test_885,4,6,I just harvested them. They're amazing! 
test_885,4,7,That's great. Have you cooked anything with them yet?
test_885,4,8,So far I've just been eating them raw. Fresh veggies are the best!
test_885,4,9,"They are, especially tomatoes. Though a hummus dip from the shops with the peppers and cucumbers would be tasty too. "
test_885,4,10,I agree. I do love hummus.
test_885,4,11,Do you have plans for the weekend?
test_886,4,0,"Three days ago, I had the pleasure of meeting the boy that my daughter is dating. He seems like a good lad, very respectful and committed to the relationship. I am much more relieved than I was when I first heard of their relationship, I am sure my daughter will be fine."
test_886,4,1,"Yeah, the dating part does worry me. It seems to really drive home the fact that your children are not little kids anymore. You are further along in the process than I am. Any advice?"
test_886,4,2,"It is a challenge to say the least. Letting go is hard. I am new to this dating thing, but the only advice I have now is to try to trust your kiddo! Let them live a little so they can make mistakes and learn from them. "
test_886,4,3,Your right. I assume when they are well into teenage land they are ninety percent done anyway. When did you first allow your daughter to date? 
test_886,4,4,You are right! I let my daughter start to date when she got into high school. That environment is so large and social that I feel it would be suffocating to not let her spread her wings a bit. 
test_886,4,5,"That makes sense. You spend so much time protecting them that it seems so foreign to realize my job is to make sure that are fully functioning, independent, productive members of society. To stand back and let them rise or fall is very daunting to think about."
test_886,4,6,Trust me it does not get any easier when that time comes either. There is a pit in my stomach any time my daughter leaves the house. But I do see a change in our relationship since I gave her freedom and she seems to respect me and engage more. 
test_886,4,7,True. I suppose the upside is the constant shuttling her from place to place will no longer be an issue. Is she already talking about getting her own car?
test_886,4,8,"It is nice sometimes! She only drives her car to school, activities and social events that are during the day. I am still not comfortable with her driving at night with all the crazies in the world. "
test_886,4,9,My oldest is already trying to sell me on the idea that he needs his own car. He keeps telling me how owning his own car will take so much work off my shoulders. He is definitely doing the hard sell.
test_886,4,10,"Good for him! You have to be proud of his ""go get it"" mentality! "
test_886,4,11,Absolutely. I applaud his effort and told him I will match him dollar for dollar and/or up to 2500 for the purchase. He has already starting mowing lawns.
test_889,4,0,Do you travel anywhere on your houseboat or do you just stay in one place?
test_889,4,1,I enjoy traveling all over on my houseboat. It is a little bit of an older boat so I can not take it out too far in fear that I will hit some rough water. But it is nice to travel around the lake during nice weather. You can come out on the boat sometime.
test_889,4,2,I would love that. Have you had the houseboat long?
test_889,4,3,"Not too long, I have lived on the houseboat for the last 5 years. I bought it off of one of my mom's work colleagues, he had inherited it from family and did not want to put in the time and effort to fix it up. It has given me a great place to stay while I work on my masters."
test_889,4,4,That was super lucky. Are you quite handy then? Have you had much joy looking for graduate jobs?
test_889,4,5,"I am not very handy, but through trial and error and many YouTube videos I have been able to figure it out. It took me nearly a year to complete all the maintenance done on the boat. And yes, I have gotten a job at the local museum as a curator. "
test_889,4,6,Youtube is the greatest so learning things. Well-done on completing the maiteance
test_889,4,7,"Thank you so much. You mentioned before that you are scared of water, but you are more than welcome to come visit me on the houseboat any day. If you would like, we can leave it docked and maybe that will lessen your fear. You can bring your kids too."
test_889,4,8,"I have booked swimming lessons, so hopefully I will become less scared. I think I'll leave the kids at home. I don't want them picking up my fear. And congrats on the new job. Are you liking it?"
test_889,4,9,"Oh good, I am happy to hear that you are committing to swimming lessons. Yes, I have been enjoying my job very much! It has been such a joy to interact with all of the historical art that the museum acquires."
test_889,4,10,"Yes, I start next week. I've even bought a costume so I'm really committed now. Great that's you enjoy your job. Do you have a lot of colleagues?"
test_889,4,11,"You will have to keep me updated on  your endeavor. No, there are not many of us that work at the museum. The museum employs only 50 people, and there are only 5 other people within my department. But I do like them all. "
test_891,4,0,"I discovered a new memoir a day ago that I have started to read, and I think you might be interested in reading it as well. It also can be found as an audio book, with several narrators that you might enjoy and like listening to. "
test_891,4,1,Oh! Who is it about?
test_891,4,2,"The book is titles ""Cant Hurt Me"" and it is a memoir for David Groggins. He talks about his transformation from young adult into a US Armed Forces elite."
test_891,4,3,"Oh wow! I'll have to get it! It would be nice to be able to see things from the perspective of someone who went into the military, it's such a different world than being a civilian!"
test_891,4,4,"Yes, it is really a good read. The story locks you in from the very beginning as he details his childhood of poverty, racial prejudice, and physical abuse. Through his 40% rule on mentality, he transformed him self from depression into the only man in history to complete elite training as a Navy SEAL, Army Ranger, and Air Force Tactical Air Controller."
test_891,4,5,That's a heck of a resume he built! So far the only elite training I've ever completed was being an elite snoozer. It's so hard to get out of my cozy bed for my morning run somedays!
test_891,4,6,"Hahaha an elite snoozer! How funny! I can definitely relate to that. But, David Groggins argues that most of us only tap into 40% of our capabilities we must push past that pain and fear threshold to achieve our potential. It has really changed my life since I began implementing it."
test_891,4,7,That sounds so inspirational! I think I'll enjoy reading it! How are you doing today?
test_891,4,8,"I am doing fantastic today, thank you for asking. Have you read any good memoirs lately? I would love a recommendation from you."
test_891,4,9,"I just started reading Negroland by Margo Jefferson, and it's a real page turner! I love how she describes what it was like in their own little cultural corner of Chicago when she was growing up. "
test_891,4,10,"Oh, interesting. I will definitely pick that up when I am at the library next. Where did you first hear about this book?"
test_891,4,11,"Honestly? I googled for some good memoirs. I wanted to find something that gave me a view into a different culture, so I just shopped around and found it!"
test_892,4,0,"My chickens have been laying eggs with very orange yolks lately, you would love them."
test_892,4,1,That is so cool! Do they taste better than regular eggs with yellow yolks?
test_892,4,2,"I'm not sure, but maybe I'll do a taste comparison. My kids love the color, though. And any way I can get my kids to eat eggs is a good thing."
test_892,4,3,"My mom says I hated eggs as a kid, too. She had to mix them into my other foods without me knowing to get me to eat them. What kind of foods do your kids like?"
test_892,4,4,"Pretty much anything, but I try to give them foods that they can recognize. We're not vegans, so it's pretty easy to make meals for them. I try to stay away from too much processed foods, too. I'm not a health nut, but I want my kids to eat a variety of foods. What about you? What do you like to eat?"
test_892,4,5,"Well, I really like steak but lately I have trying to do a vegan diet so I've been eating a lot of raw vegetables. Hopefully healthy eating will help me get that track scholarship! "
test_892,4,6,"Yes, healthy eating is good for a healthy body. But don't forget, you need your protein. You're still growing and you need your strength. Obviously you can get your protein from a vegan diet, but it can be quite restrictive. Sorry, that's the mom in me coming out! Ha!"
test_892,4,7,"That's exactly what my mom said when I told her I was going vegan. You moms are all alike, lol. I have been trying to eat a lot of nuts a few times a day to make sure I get enough protein. Do you have any other suggestions for vegan protein? "
test_892,4,8,"Yes, we're all alike! HaHa! Well, there's tofu of course. There are lots of ways to prepare it. And all those plant based meat products are good, too. Or so I've heard. I've never actually tried it, though. You can always take supplements, but I would go for natural sources of protein myself."
test_892,4,9,That's a great idea! I will look up some tofu recipes today. You seem to know a lot about nutrition. Did you take any classes in that field when you were in college? Or is it just something you learn from growing food yourself?
test_892,4,10,No no classes. It's just something you learn on your own when you have kids. Plus being on a farm makes you look at nutrition a lot. You have to make sure your animals are healthy or else you go out of business!
test_892,4,11,"Well you really know your foods, so I bet you raise great quality meat. Do you every sell your meats to individuals? I'd love to buy some (as soon as I'm done being vegan, that is.)"
test_894,4,0,Is it difficult to go to and from work in the winter?
test_894,4,1,"No, Winters are not too bad here. We rarely get any snow at all. Usually it's just a bit chilly and raining that time of year."
test_894,4,2,"that doesnt sound bad at all, especially compared to the winters in Maine."
test_894,4,3,"Not like Maine at all. I been skiing in Maine, so I know all about how cold it gets there. Do you ever go skiing?"
test_894,4,4,"There is great skiing in Maine, Im not the best at it but i do look forward to giving it a go this winter! "
test_894,4,5,That's exciting. My brother lives in Boston and goes to Maine all of the time. He has a snowmobiling camp there.
test_894,4,6,"That is too cool, do you ever go snowmobiling in the winter with him?"
test_894,4,7,"I haven't been on a snowmobile since I was a kid. My parents used to take us all the time. But, Seattle is so far away from my family in New England, that I generally only visit in the Summer."
test_894,4,8,"Summer travel is definitely easier with that much of a distance, do you generally fly or drive since you have a car?"
test_894,4,9,I can't imagine driving that far. It's take me a month to go back and forth. I barely put any miles at all on my car. I probably put more miles on my dinghy than I do my car.
test_894,4,10,Living on a lake i can see how that makes sense. Do you use your bicycle more than your car?
test_894,4,11,"Not really. My typical routine is take the dinghy to the dock and then walk to the cafe for work from there. I actually park my car at work, I sometimes go days without using it."
test_897,4,0,"I have just finished up creating a couple of designs to be displayed in an art gallery, and I am happy on how they turned out. I would like to show them to you, so I can get some feedback on how they look. You can even try them and see how they tastes, that way I know whether people that visit the galley will both like seeing them and tasting them as well."
test_897,4,1,"Well, I'm not really sure how great my opinion on art is, but I will try my best. I still don't think I really have the eye for it, though."
test_897,4,2,"Don't worry, art is extremely subjective. All I need are your honest impressions of the work."
test_897,4,3,"Okay - I'll try my best. I'm actually really excited to check it out. I mean, I always liked when bands had really cool artwork on their albums, so I guess it can't be much different than that!"
test_897,4,4,That reminds me I know of your obsession with Black Sabbath but I wondered if there are any other groups you were interested in. I have an extra Kool & The Gang tee that I think you would love. It gave me the idea to expand into edible clothing as a side exhibit.
test_897,4,5,"Yeah, I don't think anyone is more obsessed with Sabbath than I am. I literally owe thousands on my credit cards just from buying merch, it's honestly a little pathetic. But hey, I mean, Ozzy Osbourne, right? But hell yeah dude, I'll take a Kool & the Gang t-shirt, I love anything retro. "
test_897,4,6,If that's the case we should take some time to get together to go through my collection. I have several duplicates that I was going to donate but I would much rather give them to someone who I know will truly appreciate them.
test_897,4,7,"Okay, that sounds awesome. I'll be more than happy to buy some of it off you if you're willing to part with it. Do you have any Black Sabbath vinyls? Finding those in a good condition can be really hard."
test_897,4,8,"No, my collection does not extend into music. Let me check with my friend Kevin. He has quite a background in music and has become quite a collector of all things related."
test_897,4,9,"Awesome. When are you free? I'd really like to meet up soon, if at all possible. I work a lot, so I really don't have a lot of free time."
test_897,4,10,I was just thinking about your schedule. I am still in the creative zone so my schedule is fluid at the moment. Are you free this Tuesday. I have the whole day free.
test_897,4,11,"I would be free Tuesday evening after work, I think. I would just need a little time to go home and clean up a little, first. Also, I've been wanting to ask, but have you eaten any specialty meats lately?"
test_898,4,0,Do you still want to adopt out your new resucue kitten?
test_898,4,1,"Yes, I have just finished filling out and submitting all of the adoption paperwork to the animal rescue. And good news, all kittens are feeling better and are healthy again. I love them."
test_898,4,2,That's great news! Do you have any names picked out for them or are you going to keep their names?
test_898,4,3,I do not have any names picked out for them yet. I have been trying to get to know their personalities better before I give them a name. Two of them are very spunky and one is shy. Maybe I will give them a Mandarin name! Do you have any recommendations as you are learning Mandarin?
test_898,4,4,"Hm, maybe Zhao for one of them! I always thought that name sounded cool"
test_898,4,5,"Oh, how interesting! I have a friend who's surname is Zhao. What does Zhao mean in Mandarin?"
test_898,4,6,"I believe it's just the name of a state, it doesn't really have a meaning. "
test_898,4,7,"Oh, okay. Are you able to adopt any cats since you have a parrot? I do not know if those two species get along."
test_898,4,8,"I can! My parrot would be fine with the extra friend, I would just need to train the kitten to see him as a friend rather than a foe, ha!"
test_898,4,9,I will pass on any training tips that I acquire as I train the new kittens. My older cat is so mellow that I have never had any issues training her. But two on the little kittens seem like they will be a handful to train. 
test_898,4,10,"That's be great, thanks! Kittens sound like a lot of work but i'm sure it'll get done. "
test_898,4,11,"I am always diligent to have well trained pets, it is bad for owners to allow their animals to behave crazily. What kind of training did you do for your parrot, Taisha?"
test_900,4,0,How is the new role at work going?
test_900,4,1,"So far it's working out well. It is a bit different overseeing more people than I used to, so I am still getting used to that. Overall I think I performing okay though! Did you finish that essay you were working on last week for school?"
test_900,4,2,I completely forgot I mentioned that to you!  I actually got it done a couple days ago. My husband is my best editor and I just got it updated with his suggestions.  I think it should get a good grade.
test_900,4,3,"Aw, I love to hear about spouses supporting the education and work of their significant others. How does he feel about you becoming a teacher?"
test_900,4,4,"He was the one that suggested it!  It was actually my plan and then we met and started having children.  After our third went to Kindergarten, my husband asked if I was ready to go after that dream again. "
test_900,4,5,"He sounds amazing, you certainly hit the jackpot in finding him! Now that my career is pretty steady I have been thinking a lot about getting out there are trying to meet someone. Where did you meet your husband?"
test_900,4,6,It was kind of a funny story.  I was sort of crushing on his best friend at the time who was my co-worker.  So we had a co-workers thing where he brought my future husband and we just hit it off!  I know that your guy is out there just waiting for you.  Just stay confident and don't rush things.
